rdf:Description.lla:note: Discharged - Arrested for stabbing a fellow crew member in the leg whilst refusing to return to the ship after shore leave.
Registry of Indenture at Liverpool on 1866-11-08
Registry of Indenture at Aberystwyth on 1868-05-19

Performs cook duties after Lynch is discharged. Caught stealing twice. 23rd May - Property valued at four shillings and sixpence. 13th August - He has stolen two books to the value of nine shillings and six pence. The value of the items is deducted from his wages.
Much written in Log Book regarding his misconduct and insubordination
Much written in Log Book regarding his misconduct and insubordination
Registry of Indenture: 21st. May 1868 at Aberystwyth
